  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed alteration and increase in height to the dwellings roof ridge would form a dominant and discordant feature within the host terrace which displays a uniform, consistent and legible roof ridge height throughout. The addition would undermine and cause visual harm to this existing context and is exacerbated by its visibility from both the public and private realm. The proposals are therefore contrary to policies 7.4, 7.6 and 7.8 of the London Plan, policies CS8 and CS9 of the Core Strategy 2011 and policy DM2.1 of the Development Management Plan 2013, Islington's Urban Design Guide 2017 and the NPPF 2019."
